The paper deals with cooperative game theory and communication networks, which are both covered by the sub-category cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Making). The use of Device-to-device (D2D) communication suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses file transfer and partitioning, which are topics covered by cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of stable partitions in coalitional games suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with energy expenditure reduction, which is a topic covered by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
